## Introduction

This unit introduces our course, and explains how everything is going to work.
It is also the course syllabus.

The learning objectives for this unit are:

-   You know how to navigate around Carnap.io
-   You know how to contact me, and when my office hours are
-   You understand the course policies, including
    -   the assignment structure 
    -   the grading scheme
    -   the retake policy
    -   the collaboration units
    -   how due dates work

Every chapter's reading assignment begins with a statement of objectives just like this!

To complete this reading assignment, you need to answer all the questions. Here is what a
question looks like:

```{.QualitativeProblem .MultipleChoice points=10}
1 To "complete" this reading assignment, I must
|*answer all the included questions.
|answer most of the included questions. 
```

:::{.reaction .correct ex=1}
Great! You've correctly answered your first reading question! Notice the
progress bar at the top of the page, which helps you keep track of your
progress.
:::

